.TH "scsi_send_eh_cmnd" 9 "scsi_send_eh_cmnd" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
scsi_send_eh_cmnd \- submit a scsi command as part of error recovery
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" scsi_send_eh_cmnd
.BI "(struct scsi_cmnd *scmd "  ","
.BI "unsigned char *cmnd "  ","
.BI "int cmnd_size "  ","
.BI "int timeout "  ","
.BI "unsigned sense_bytes "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "scmd" 12
SCSI command structure to hijack
.IP "cmnd" 12
CDB to send
.IP "cmnd_size" 12
size in bytes of \fIcmnd\fP
.IP "timeout" 12
timeout for this request
.IP "sense_bytes" 12
size of sense data to copy or 0
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is used to send a scsi command down to a target device
as part of the error recovery process. See also \fBscsi_eh_prep_cmnd\fP above.

Return value:
SUCCESS or FAILED or NEEDS_RETRY
